Criterion Vs. Criteria


Meaning-  'Criterion' is singular whereas 'criteria' is the plural form.

Example- - Earlier there was just one criterion for being called a good student i.e., getting good marks.
                    -The academic policy clearly elucidates the criteria for awarding internal marks.
                
(More examples- Datum/ data, Agendum/ Agenda, Index/ Indices, Basis/ Bases, Analysis/ Analyses, Curriculum/ Curricula,
Formula/ Formulae, Hypothesis/ Hypotheses, Phenomenon/ Phenomena, symposium/ symposia, crisis/crises, etc.)
